Confession ⬇️

I’m totally addicted to seeing you win! I LOVE when you guys give feedback and I directly see and hear the impact I’m having on your businesses!

I remember how it felt just winging my posts on Instagram, not knowing what will resonate or fail. Using my own strategy I’ve grown almost 400,000 followers this year!

I wrote my growth guide to simplify this process, there are simple steps you can read and apply to learn how to get IG working for you! 

Don’t believe me?

HUGE thank you for your incredible guide. It has given me the confidence to delve into a world I am totally unfamiliar with. Not only that, it has given me the structure I need to build out a strategy and a plan for tackling our social pages, instead of feeling around in the dark!”

Get this simple 1 photo Story Effect ⬇️

Save this SECRET  instagram filter you can use for any image you’d like to promote or share.

First off, don’t forget to SAVE this post so you don’t forget the steps

Instructions are below ⬇️

- tap to begin a new REEL, add any image from your camera roll, tap next and tap the sparkles button 

- Tap the magnifying glass, search for the effect “cubic” apply this and save the video it creates.

- Now begin a new story, and load the video you just created in reels section.

- now go to the original image in your photo album, hold down until you see the shimmer effect and copy and paste the photo back into Instagram

- Now go to your sticker tab again, type instagram frame and choose the same one as me, resize so it fits nicelyinto the photo in the centre of the screen. Be sure to place the subject of your photo over the frame.

- go to your sticker tab, and link, add the link to your business or brand, and place this on the white frame. Be sure to add custom text a few words long, as this will act as bottom of your photo frame too.

- Now go to sticker tab one more time, type click, and add this to the frame.

- Finally, go to your sticker tab and search for  likes. Add the same one as me to complete this effect.

This is such a simple effect you could use over and over again with different images and links as you need! Let me know if this tutorial helped.

I share brand new ideas daily to help inspire your instagram content and help you grow your audience and learn your way around instagram!

caption.text:
Stop shooting boring video!

Having a video with movement in is a great way to stop your audience from scrolling by, we call this a visual hook and it’s key to success on Instagram.

Now, I work from home alone and don’t often have anyone to help me film content…this tip is one I have used over and over.

Use this tip to add movement to your static videos inside instagram, and without the need to edit!

- tap to begin a new reel, go to camera, and then select the sparkle icon

- now go to the magnifying glass and search “body frame” press the screen, and the shutter button to begin recording

- stand back, and as you move the camera will follow you side to side, and even zoom in and out. 

Adding movement makes your videos more visually engaging increasing watching time and hopefully reach!

If you enjoyed this tip, make sure you’re following me! I share new tips daily to make your instagram growth journey that bit easier!

Did you know about this tip?

caption.text:
Build curiosity with this⬇️

Meta has confirmed “watch time” is a metric they measure within the Instagram algorithm,  This reel idea is a great way to increase watch time, and make an announcement.

Don’t forget to save this post as you won’t want to forget these steps! 

- Start by loading the image you would like to share, begin a screen recording, and hold your thumb down on the top top right hand side of your screen. This will blur the image, as you raise your thumb up the image will become clearer.

- Once you have videoed yourself taking the image from blurry to clear, and the screen recording.

- Now begin a new real, load the screen recording you just made, and trim the beginning and end to leave just the blurry to clear part of the video.

- Now go to your stickers tab, type in “ dotted lines” and add the dotted lines to the left and right of the screen to give the image of a film strip.

- Now you can add any text or stickers of your choice, I added coming soon with a space between each letter, added the original image tap to make it a circle and put it in place of the letter O.

Comment below GUIDE and I’ll whiz over my step by step guide for you follow along and start your journey into instagram growth

caption.text:
Examples ⬇️

The biggest complaint I hear is that you are busy, and making reels is complicated and time consuming. Im here to help 🫶🏻

SAVE this reel and audio 

Add a 5 second video showing what you do, sell, make, offer, create or love.

Make sure this video has some movement, add cuts, or speed it up if needed

Add text: What if you didn’t hate (add audience frustration) you just hadn’t found my account yet / another way to (add what you do)

Examples below ⬇️

What if you didn’t hate cardio you just hadn’t found my boxercise classes, another way to lose weight, have fun and smash things up without getting in trouble 

What if you didn’t hate your house, you just hadn’t found an interior designer, who works with accessible budgets and realistic living spaces for families and kids!

What if you didn’t hate buying Christmas gifts, you just hadn’t found my handmade candle store, where every present is made with love,  so you can show you care!

Drop what you do below, and who you help and let’s have a go with your business!

and make sure you’re following me, I post new ideas, tips and tricks to help make your life on instagram easier!

#instagramgrowth #iggrowth #contentcreator #smallbusinessowner #smallbusinessuk l

Super Fun Story 🐾

Fun for the weekend, This effect would work to liven up ANY image in your stories! 

Stories are a great way to share sneak peeks, or behind the scenes content with your audience, you could use this effect over and over! 

Don’t forget to SAVE this post, as you don’t want to forget the steps!

- tap and begin a new story, choose any image (or video) from your camera roll, go to effects and look for “xxinstaxx” if you don’t see the filter, I’ll save it here. You can also search and save through reels section.

- Go to your text tab, using the last font, I placed a letter on each line and move the word MOOD over to the left.

- Using the colour picker, pick a complimentary colour from inside the photo to colour your text

- Go to the stickers tab, type in café in and place your favourite coffee inside the letter O.

- Go to sticker tab again, look for the Instagram cutout feature and load your original image. Instagram will cut out the main feature and create a sticker to place on the filtered image.
 

This is such a simple effect you could use over and over again with different image and text! Let me know if this tutorial helped! If you’re struggling with all things Instagram, comment REGISTER to get early access to my brand new course; 

It’s going to take away all the stress and guesswork, so you know what to post, when and why! If you’re on the waitlist you’ll grab 20% off launch price too!

I share new idea daily to help inspire your instagram content and help you grow and learn your way around instagram! 🚀❤️

Public Service Announcement: 

if I can put on a ballgown, create a make shift sign from the bread board and strut around my local supermarket to promote my business…

…You CAN talk about YOUR business, on YOUR instagram page. 

Grab a video clip, use this audio & Try this prompt ⬇️

“If you just start doing ____ then you will ___”

If you just start regularly posting about your business online, then you will build your own online community 

If you just start tidying one drawer a day, then you will have an organised kitchen my next week

Easy Trick to Share a Reel ⬇️

Instagram has confirmed that reels are the still the best way for you to reach new audiences, but stories are the best way to connect current followers….well this hack combines both, AND looks great too!

Don’t forget to SAVE this post so you don’t forget the steps!! 

- Tap and begin a new story, tap camera, and slide through filters until you find the magnifying glass.

- type in background no1046, and tap the shutter button to take a photo. Now save this image and close the screen.

- choose the reel you would like to share, tap the airplane and share to story. Move the reel to the side, now go to sparkles tab, photo and add the image you just took,

- go to sparkles tab, type iPhone frame, add a frame to screen, then sparkles tab and type cafezim, add an animation to your cup.

- now hold down, and slide down to add the reel to the frame. 
- now just go to text tab, and add text to give context to the reel you’re sharing.

- Go to your stickers tab, type “new reel black” and choose the sticker to place on top of the reel

Anybody that taps your reel is going to get taken through to watch it. 

If you love this instagram reel idea, check out some of my others and make sure you’re following me, I share new ones every single day to help you on your instagram growth journey!

I’m always here to help you with your content, and if writing your captions is a struggle, comment HOOKS and I’ll share 100 for you to try.

caption.text:
If you struggle with growing your business or reaching the right audience on Instagram, 

Maybe you think that the number of views or how many followers you get is a direct correlation to how successful your business is? If that sounds familiar, I’m so glad you’re here. 

That used to be me, for years I grafted with the belief that 1 million followers would “change everything”. Truth couldn’t be further from that, It’s been a lesson for me, so I get it and now I’m ready to help ya out! 😉

Make sure you’re following me, @embrace_socials for more daily (tips, tricks, videos, hacks) on how to organically grow and connect using Instagram.

Reply GUIDE and u will send you over a link to the 53 page strategy I wrote, including the steps I follow to grow and attract an audience to my account.

#instagramgrowth #iggrowth #smallbusinessowner #smallbusinesslife #igtips #contentstrategy

Make a Reminder Post ⬇️

This secret Instagram feature is so clever! Instagram can actually send reminders of the event at the time or date mentioned! This effect is so versatile you could use it to highlight any date or event, for business or just a birthday coming up!

Don’t forget to save this post so you don’t forget the steps! 

- Tap and begin a new story, go to create, layout, and choose the four grid option. Add any four images you’d like I’m using birthday images, you could use any photos to suit the theme of your post.

- Once you’ve selected the images, tap the tick box. Now go to your text tab type a. Followed by nine spaces with a white background. Place the rectangle vertically in the centre of the screen.

- Go into your phones calendar, take a screenshot of any month you will be highlighting. Now go back into Instagram, to the sticker tab, and add the photo of the shotted calendar placing it on the white rectangle.

- Now go to your photo album again choose one of the original images, and place on the white rectangle.

- Now go to sticker again, and look for the countdown option, select this you can choose any date or time you’d like and add a title announcing what you are counting down to.

- Place the countdown icon onto the white rectangle when clicked, this will actually notify your audience of the event at the time specified. 

- Now add text stickers to match the theme of your announcement, I am using launch day you could use anything you would like.

- Lastly, go to your sparkles tab and look for the filter cornerdance , if you can’t find it, I have saved it to this reel and if you’re unable to find it, I have saved it to this reel

If you like this tutorial, make sure you’re following me I add new tips daily and can’t wait to help you on your Instagram growth journey!

I really hope this design helps, but if you’re looking for more support on your Instagram growth journey, type the word GUIDE below and I’ll send you a link to my 53 page growth guide I wrote you through the Instagram growth process step-by-step!
